message:
Heads up: I already applied my 'strip' edit to str.first()/str.last() in crates/typst/src/foundations/str.rs (compiles cleanly). Here's the current state of both functions so you can layer 'repeat' on top:

    pub fn first(
        &self,
        #[named]
        strip: Option<Str>,
    ) -> StrResult<Str> {
        let s = match &strip {
            Some(strip) => self.0.trim_start_matches(|c| strip.as_str().contains(c)),
            None => self.0.as_str(),
        };
        s.graphemes(true).next().map(Into::into).ok_or_else(string_is_empty)
    }

    pub fn last(
        &self,
        #[named]
        strip: Option<Str>,
    ) -> StrResult<Str> {
        let s = match &strip {
            Some(strip) => self.0.trim_end_matches(|c| strip.as_str().contains(c)),
            None => self.0.as_str(),
        };
        s.graphemes(true).next_back().map(Into::into).ok_or_else(string_is_empty)
    }

Please add your 'repeat' param as an additional #[named] arg on top of this rather than reverting my strip changes. Ping me when you've edited so I can double check the merge compiles on my end before I submit patch.txt.
